# Docs and Traceability

- Prefer citing local docs instead of restating behavior:
  - `@docs/plan.md` – execution strategy, risks, and slices.
  - `@docs/spec.md` – flows, contracts, and data rules.
  - `@docs/test-plan.md` – test inventory and red-baseline policy.
  - `@docs/traceability.md` – requirement-to-test mappings.
  - `@docs/decisions/ADR-*.md` – architectural decisions.
- When proposing a change:
  - call out which `FR-*` / `NFR-*` / `INV-*` / `SAFE-*` / `ADR-*` you are touching.
  - suggest specific `TC-*` updates (or additions) and where they live under `tests/`.
- Keep `CHANGELOG.md` and docs in sync with significant changes:
  - new or changed IDs
  - new external dependencies or infra behavior
  - any change that affects runtime modes or data boundaries.

